dataIdInfo.idPurp: Assessor's parcel data for the town of Dedham, MA.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset consists of tax parcels for Dedham, Massachusetts. Tax parcels represent property boundaries for the purpose of tax assessment. Tax parcels are not an authoritative source of property boundaries. The authoritative record of property boundaries are recorded at the Norfolk County Registry of Deeds. Only a professional land surveyor my produce a legally authoritative map of property boundaries. Mapand CAMA data updated July, 2025.

Consts.useLimit: This data may be appropriate for planning purposes. It should not be utilized where legal and surveyed property boundaries are required.

report.measDesc: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

prcStep.stepDesc: Existing GIS parcel data was converted to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase and additional data layers and tables were added.
Spatial accuracy of data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines; town boundary was verified to be coincident with MassGIS town Boundary layer. Polygon topology was updated and validated.

Updates were made to the Level II data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of May 2011 for the town's FY 2012. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. Final QA/QC tool was run.

Multipart polygons were created where necessary; internal polygon boundaries were dissolved where necessary; polygons representing legal boundaries such as easements or private right-of-ways were created. LOC_ID was generated or updated.

Overlay errors between TaxPar and OthLeg were corrected. Multilink errors between TaxPar and Assess were verified or corrected. Lotsize discrepancies between shape area in TaxPar and LOTSIZE in Assess were verified or corrected.

dataSource.srcDesc: Source data is in ESRI personal geodatabase format. This geodatabase was previously a MassGIS level 2 - compliant dataset. Original automation was from 204 tax maps at 1" = 40', in 2005.

dataLineage.statement:
Tax parcels are maintained by the Town of Dedham GIS Division. Source information includes Assessor records and recordings from the Norfolk County Registry of Deeds. MassGIS Level 3 Tax parcels are automatically generated from the source data.
This data layer was originally created as part of the Dedham Stormwater Management Plan by Woodard and Curran in 2000 with extensive QA/QC by Applied Geographics, Inc. Woodard and Curran created the digital parcel information (street right-of-ways, parcel boundaries, parcel annotation, easements and unique parcel identifiers) from 50-scale parcel mapping created by Philling Engineering in 1967. The digital planimetric mapping was used as a reference for parcel boundary placement. The then current parcel maps were used as a primary reference check to identify missing parcels in the 50-scale parcel mapping.
The assessing database from Vision Appraisal Technology (VAT) was used to determine Registry Numbers for parcels missing from the 50-scale mapping. Using Deed research techniques, Deeds and Subdivision plans for the missing parcels were then copied and all parcel information was incorporated into the digital parcel mapping.
The data layer was managed by Applied Geographics, Inc. but remained property of the Town of Dedham. Edits and updates were made annually based on information provided by the Town Assessor’s and Engineer’s office. Fiscal Year 1997, 1998 and 1999 parcel updates were incorporated by Woodard and Curran in the original project. Applied Geographics, Inc. updated the parcel data as recently in June 2007.
In 2011, Applied Geographic, Inc. updated the parcel data to conform to MassGIS Level 3 Assessors’ Parcel Mapping standard.

overview.dsoverv: Parcel data for the city of Dedham, MA. Parcel data, current as of August 2011, was upgraded to MassGIS Level III standards. Data represents boundaries of approximately 8700 properties, and corresponding information from the town's records of property assessment, including property address, use code and value. Property boundaries are current as of August 2011; property record information is current as of December 2011, and represent data for the the town's fiscal year 2012.
